comments.body:
You can COPY this function in a file and run it in Powershell 5 and Powershell 7:

```

function TestVoice{
        Add-Type -AssemblyName System.speech
        $VersionMajor=$global:PSVersionTable.PsVersion.Major
        $VersionMinor=$global:PSVersionTable.PsVersion.Major
        $Statement="This is a test of Text To Speech. Powershell Version " + $VersionMajor
        $Statement += " dot " + $VersionMinor
        Write-Host "############################" -f DarkRed
        Write-Host $Speech -f DarkRed
        
        try{
            $David=New-Object System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer
            $David.SelectVoice('Microsoft David Desktop')
            $David.Speak($Statement)
        }
        catch {
            Write-Host "ERROR: $_.Exception.Message" -b DarkRed -f Yellow
        }
}
```

@cybercastor No. You open an "issue" about a problem, please stay focus on the "current" subject.
System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer work on PowerShell 7.2 with an recent OS ( at least Microsoft Windows 10.0.19043).

Workaround : use PowerShell 7.2 + upgrade your OS or use another library
